caption: Service was quick and easy.  They are taking appropriate precautions for Covid.  The pokè bowl was not very good.  Strong mayo flavor, very small amount of protein in bowl, not very may veggie options in bowl, and way too much rice (filler) compared to the other ingredients.  Not terrible but not my favorite bowl.

Went to visit the Hapeville location to link up with my sister and nieces. It’s a small restaurant but the Poke in a bowl is a nice size! They have dry marker menus to write in to figure out your selection. The workers there are friendly and helpful. The price was perfect about $10 a bowl starting off! I took my orders to-go and when I got home it was soooo good! I can’t wait to come back home to ATL to get another bowl! This might just be a little jem in Hapeville!
Poke is awesome here

A very popular poke bowl place downtown, crowded during the lunch time. A bit limited on the choices of side, portion for protein is generous. Food is fresh and prepared fast. No frills place. Slightly pricey but acceptable given the location.
Very Nice Sushi!!!
I absolutely  love this place.

ALWAYS out of something on the menu. I've gone and they've been completely out of salmon, seaweed salad, tuna, and rice. Not at the same time, mind you, but still. Delicious food when they have it all together.
Love, love, love their poké bowl...
Nasty place. Your worker needs to check y’all bowl before you give it to a consumer. Found a live bug in the bottom of my bowl. Won’t come back to this place

We had lunch at the new Fish Bowl Poke in Toco Hill. It opened yesterday. I ordered a,bowl with rice & salad, tuna, shrimp. This is a nice concept. The food was very good but there was something in the bowl a little too salty for me. I could not figure our what it was. It is a small restaurant with mostly family style seating. It's not a great atmosphere inside & I suspect when it is crowded it won't be very comfortable. This is more of a take out place for me. Not sure how well it will do in this location.
Pretty good but prices are a little high for what you get
Best Poke' in town or out of town
The best Poke spot in Atlanta!

Wow!!! Amazing food. Did not expect this caliber of quality when we walked in. But we were deliciously surprised. I had a steak dish with rice. Meat was tender, veggies amazing and rice cooked to perfection. I highly recommend this place. Zagat please come out and rate this place, they deserve it. Also one more delight, prices were very reasonable.
Place was delicious! Great costumer service! Very clean!
Best Poke in downtown ATL - very quick dispite the long line during lunch

My mother and I really enjoy Poke, especially during the summer, but this is run by someone who thought Poke is all the rage lets open a Poke bar. We ordered two 2 scope bowls which were $27 dollars, limited toppings , no veggies to select from at all and you pay extra for the krab, seaweed salad and avocado which is typical, but those are your addtional veggie options. Opps they do offer green or red onions at no charge, sesume seeds and the like. The scopps are not what you get at other Poke bars, they are not even scoops. Also they forgot to put my advocado on my bowl. I went up and they looked at my ticket, did not say anything and took a thin piece of avocado and when i say thin I meam thin and place it on my bowl. I looked at my disappointing bowl and had to laugh.
Rice seemed burned.
LOVE THIS PLACE SO MUCH
Loveee this spot! Very fresh! I wish they were open on the weekends but I get lunch spots!

caption: Poke
My spot right here boi

First thing I realized when I walked in was the small amount of choices for toppings. Very limited (compared to other poke places). Then by the time I placed my order, it was $18 for a bowl of poke (with only free add-ons) and a small fountain drink. That’s a bit over priced in my opinion for a cafeteria style restaurant. I had given my name with the order, but when my food was ready she didn’t call out my order. She only placed it on the counter. I got my cup for my fountain drink, but there was no ice so I got a hot soda. There were no lids left and the straws were shorter than the cup. The bowl was poorly made. Everything wasn’t balanced, just all on one side. The food did not taste bad. It was actually pretty good! Overall a 3 out 5 experience. The owners have some tightening up to do if they plan to keep customers at those prices.

So when you first walk in you take a piece of paper and you write down your choices you choose your base then your protein and all your toppings and the sauce on top. I didn't like the way they put in the orders it made it to where someone who's behind me to get there for the first because she put their piece of paper on top of mine before she gave it to the people making the food. The Poke came out and it was really good probably some of the best poke I've ever had. They didn't have any special ingredients like other poke places it was pretty basic I would have preferred something off the wall like pineapples or something else that is different like some other poke places you can find in Atlanta.
I. Love. Poke. Bowls. This spot hit the spot and I'll def be back. Reasonably priced with large portions!
They were out of most of their protein options, and sushi rice. They get 5 stars anyway, because the food was amazing.
Good pricing for the amount of food!!

This one of the best poke spots in town! They seem to have more options than most of the other chains. Always crowded around lunch but they move quickly and it's never taken over 5-10 minutes to get my food. Staff is always friendly and ingredients always very fresh.
Fast and friendly to Uber Eats drivers
Got sick after eating pork bowl here
Friendly staff. They informed me there wasn't anymore shrimp after I ordered and there weren't bags for to go orders. Octopus was over cooked. Less rice, more toppings.
Friendly service and great Poke.
Great food with excellent service!
Great fast sushi bowl food
My favorite place on campus to grab a bite to eat while still having some left for latef
This place is really the only reason why I miss college at GSU.

The selection of food can vary, so it really depends on your choices.  I always come back here because their food is always fresh and healthy (in a way, it looks so, don't quote me on it 🤣). I usually get the shrimp bowl with salad but sometimes I got the tofu bowl too (cause they do it right!).  Been going to them for two years now and the taste doesn't change. You should definitely continue going there especially if you're a health-concious type of person. The price is not too cheap but that's what you get with the quality.
Fresh great food
So good!!
Overpriced for what you received.  Atlanta has a lot more to offer.

My poke bowl was so delicious. And if you don’t finish, you can save it in the refrigerator for later. My poke bowl had salad and rice for the base then tofu, red onions, green onions, sesame seeds, and a spicy aioli for the sauce. Very good spot for vegetarians like myself.
Healthy and delicious lunch option!
I tried the Poke bowl with Tofu Option. It came with fresh salad and delicious Tofu. Liked it.
Completely addicted to this place.
OMG, finally something good to eat that's close to my Hawaiian roots.

My first time here has a great experience and every experience after food is always fresh and great quality . Parking can be hard because it’s in the heart of the city so DoorDash or ubereats is also an option !!
Nice dishes

This place is nice. I like being able to take my time in ordering and know what I've already selected. The dry-erase type menu/ordering system makes it easy to see what all you've selected. The service is fast and friendly. There is some seating inside.
Had a Uber eats pickup from here. Fast and friendly service.

I found this place in Nov 2017 and have been hooked ever since. I probably visit twice a month, and the ingredients are always fresh and very tasty. I like the wide variety of options to choose from when making my bowl, and the prices are reasonable. This is one of my favorite downtown lunch spots.
I eat here at least twice a week.  The best poke in Atlanta! Get there before 12 to beat the lunch crowd.
Great food but a little pricey.

I really like that avocado is included in the toppings and doesn't cost extra. I also like that they have bottles of aioli available for you to add it yourself if you want. There's not really any parking, so it's mostly for people who work or go to school downtown.
Nice place, great food and friendly staff

I love this place and I will soon work here!! It has so much delicious choices and I really want to eat some almost every day! I would love to serve all the customers here! You can even watch the chefs do the work behind the counter!
Tasty quick poké ideal for lunch. I wish they would ditch the plastic bowls though. It's 2018 and there are lots of alternatives that don't generate a perpetual waste management problem like that.
My order came (uber eats) with none of the selected toppings on it. just rice, spring mix and meat...... super bland disappointing experience when you are expecting fish roe and other yummy things.
Good poke experience. A lot of options.  Have had several good meals there.  A little pricey for everyday, but it is sushi grade fish.  My only complaint would be a limited soda selection.

This small location is more of a take out restaurant than a sit down and eat restaurant. The lunch crowds are bustling, so be prepared to wait a bit to get your poke. The staff are fast and cordial, which helps the line move along. The bowls are part make your own, part choose from a template. They're good and priced well. Be aware that the space can be a bit tight if you're in a wheelchair.

This is my go-to lunch spot during the work week. The food is consistently delicious, service is always accurate and fast. Their method with filling out your order on a sheet of paper is super effective! :) I'm so glad they have a rewards system because I love this place!

I would eat here everyday if I could afford too. Best place to eat on broad Street if you want to feel full, fullfiled, and get a friendly and quick customer service. Expect delays if you want to go at peak lunch hour in downtown could have to wait up to several 7-9 minutes if the store is packed!!
First time I tried poke. If you like sushi, you’ll like this place. You make your own custom order with your choice of seafood, rice, and toppings.

Very yummy fresh delightful salad bowl with choices of tuna..salmon and other fish selections.  Best spot on this street. Highly recommended!

When I went to college at Georgia State, this place was an absolute godsend. Eating here is one of the only things I miss about living in Atlanta.
